  Q. Approving redistricting map for Grand County voting districts (Commissioner Walker)
  **Presentation** Kevin discussed the redistricting maps and offered the most popular suggestions for final review. Kevin discussed the mapping program and the retained redistricting consultants. Kevin discussed the maps that were generally considered most popular, balanced, and rational. Chris noted that to the greatest extent possible the districts should match federal and state boundaries. Kevin discussed the school board boundaries and the extension into San Juan County. Christina noted a redistricting can’t force someone into having to run for office before their elected term is up.
  
  ## Motion by Sarah Stock to:
  
  1. Adopt map “Contiguous Neighborhoods” as the new Grand County Commission districts. These districts will also serve as voter participation areas and local school board districts with the modifications discussed during the meeting (Jackson Street, City Boundary, etc.)
     2.Adopt the assignment of sitting members to new districts as described in the packet.
  
  ## Motion seconded by Trish Hedin
  
  **Discussion** Trish offered thanks to Kevin and Sarah for all the work on the maps. Gabriel noted both finalists are good options, but suggested support for the “Contiguous Neighborhoods” map.
  
